data.name: RichTextBox4.Text
data.value:
The VB.NET command sapgui.ReadGrid(dt) is used to read the data from the sap grid.
You can enter function codes in the transaction by using sapgui.Enter("/FC") e.g. sapgui.Enter("/8") for F8 key. Please have a look at <http://www.sapdesignguild.org/resources/references/nv_fkeys_ref2_e.htm> for more information.

data.name: RichTextBox1.Text
data.value:
Select a customer to display a list of all orders.
You can doubleclick on the order number in table to select the order.
Click on "show order details" then.
Please choose a template-directory first for the saved HTML-files to be saved into.

data.name: RichTextBox2.Text
data.value:
For loading the list of orders SAP GUI Scripting is used: Transaction VA05 will be called and the data of the SAP grid is then read by VB.NET command "sapgui.ReadGrid(dt)" where dt is a DataTable object.
Details to an order are read in transaction VA03 by using the commands sapgui.GetField(Name of field) and sapgui.ReadTree(dt). The DataObject dt needs than to be converted to a TreeView VB.NET Object. You can see the struture of an SAP Tree below the converted VB.NET tree on tab "Document Flow".

data.name: RichTextBox5.Text
data.value:
Connection: Please provide the logon and connection parameters used by .NET connector and GuiNET (SAP GUI Scripting Interface). The password will be saved encrypted into the config.ini.
E-Mail: You can provide logon-data for an SMTP host here if you want to send an e-mail with VB.NET.
Misc.: Please provide your GuiNET licensekey here. GuiNET can not be used without licensekey when used in a standalone project.
